The paper describes a framework for developing test chips, which involves hardware design and validation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) category. Additionally, the paper mentions domain-specific architectures (DSAs) and programmable hosts, which are relevant to the Architecture (cs.AR) category. The paper also discusses the challenges of the design process, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper mentions the use of agile development practices and code generation tools, which are relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the full chip design, which could fall under the Electromagnetics (cs.EM) category.
